<br>
On large targets that can gate or if you have an enchanter with you, your best bet is to have them seive. A full raid party of 20 melee kicking, slamming and bashing can still allow a CH or a Gate to take place. Trading damage output for a few more random chances at stunning a mob is not worth it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 6:53:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You could have 20 warriors with max bash skill bashing a mob like crazy and it might interrupt a CH once in 20 tries, if you are lucky.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
