<br>
I'm a 58 SK and I make it my prime duty to stun caster mobs when I'm in a group (with melee secondary and casting tertiary) as it prevents unnecessary complete heals, nukes and other irritating spells that mobs cast to throw you off.<br>
<br>
The best example of this that i can pull off the top of my head is the upper kobolds in Velks, if you're fighting a champion and a priest pops near you and begins healing, if that champion is almost dead the priest will damn near ALWAYS CH the damned thing just as it's about to die, making your job over 100 percent longer and harder than it has to be.<br>
<br>
If I see that priest pop and realise it's casting i dive forward and bash the crap out of it until the champion is dead.<br>
<br>
Sure a cleric/pally/etc can always stun, but more often than not their attention is elsewhere (healing, tanking etc) and it's not always possible to switch targets rapidly.<br>
<br>
The moral of this baffling rant is: &quot;If you've got bash/slam/kick and it stuns the mobs, USE IT&quot;<br>
<br>
