<br>
I would be surprised if it dropped your total damage output by 10%, if at all. Hybrids on the other hand face a much larger penalty in damage output if you make them bash. Why, you might ask? Because they can't dual wield. And 1hs weapons are generally crap. A hybrid's damage output can easily fall by 50% or more if they go to the 1h + shield combo. That's a hell of a lot more lost damage than a warrior ghetto bashing.<br>
<br>
Then again, this thread does seem to say a bit about the classes themselves - warriors are one-dimensional fighting machines. Hybrids do a little of everything - including bashing. Of course, the irony here is that warriors get the highest bashing cap in the game. Too bad it's wasted.<br>
<br>
<br>
And for those who don't know, if a mob's casting can be interrupted via stun, a landed bash will ALWAYS interrupt it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/28/02 4:22:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I would be surprised if it dropped your total damage output by 10%, if at all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
