<br>
Being new to the warrior game myself with a vah shir I have leveling up they don't get inate slam either which is b/s imho.  If you're too big to get in FV buildings I think you should get slam but that's neither here nor there.<br>
<br>
Swapping a shield in and out... I don't play with my inventory screen up all the time.  I can't have a shield constantly sitting on my cursor either.  So, what's the best way to switch that shield in and out without constantly having to bring up my inventory nor have it always sitting on my cursor?<br>
<br>
On the bash discussion though...<br>
<br>
You shouldn't be pulling mobs so far away that gating is a problem in the first place.  If you're pulling mobs from so far away that mobs are respawning again in between where you pulled it from and where you are then you are over pulling or not moving closer to where you really need to be.  Yes, gating wanderers are a bitch and I agree they are the rare exception.  But there are still more options than ghetto bashing available.<br>
<br>
On a CH issue... you either seive the hell out of it or those wizards need to be saving mana to nuke it to oblivion once it gets to CH or Gate stage.  Some form of lure is going to work on it and it's a hell of a lot more reliable than ghetto bashing.  It's the wizard's job to know when that is (yes, you wizards do need to pay a little more attention than just button pressing.)  If you have no other options beyond ghetto bashing a mob you, as a guild, didn't come prepared for the encounter to begin with and the blame is not entirely on the warriors.  Most guilds do have a lead tank and the rest &quot;should&quot; carry shields with them just for that one time in their entire EQ career where it was absolutely needed.  However, I have yet to see a warrior ever put on a shield nor have I ever seen a situation where there wasn't another and better option available.<br>
<br>
&quot;And for those who don't know, if a mob's casting can be interrupted via stun, a landed bash will ALWAYS interrupt it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, however, the issue here is mobs that aren't stunnable which started this discussion.  If the mob is stunnable then stun the damn thing to begin with rather than resort to ghetto bashing and losing any amount of dps no matter how small the loss might be.<br>
<br>
