<br>
<br>
For those warrior types who don't have the slam skill, here is an effective method for disrupting those pesky spell casting mobs.  I call it slash and bash, but there are those who call it......Tim?<br>
<br>
You'll need to be duel-wielding to pull this off.  It can be done with a 2H weapon, but it's more difficult.  Besides, duel wielding against casters is always a good thing.   Oh, and because kick and bash are mutually exclusive, you shouldn't be kicking at all while using this tactic.<br>
<br>
First of all, you'll need to set up your hotkey slots so that at a minimum, you have the bash skill and your offhand weapon slot present (see picture below for more detail).  To get the offhand weapon slot into the hotkey slots, simply hit 'i' to bring up the inventory window and click and drag the weapon slot to an open hotkey slot.<br>
<br>
When attacking a caster mob, get your shield out and hold it on your mouse cursor.  Now the tricky part.  Watch for the the spell casting message &quot;Bignastymob_05 begins to cast a spell&quot;.  When you see that, click on the offhand weapon slot, which will cause you to equip your shield (your weapon will appear on your mouse cursor).  Immediately press the number of the bash button.  Finally, reclick in the offhand slot to reequip your weapon and place the shield back on the mouse.<br>
By doing so, you usually will not miss a round of battle with your offhand, and you get a chance of interrupting a spell.<br>
I keep the mouse hovered over the weapon slot so it only takes a fraction of a second to complete the sequence.  My bash button is number 4, so the sequence is click-4-click.<br>
<br>
Couple of other tips.<br>
<br>
1)  Keep an open inventory slot for your shield and drag that slot to the hotkey slots as well.  This makes it easier to equip when that caster mob is pulled back to camp.  You don't have to go fishing around your backpacks for it.  This isn't shown in the screenshot below.<br>
<br>
2)  Change the text color of the mobs spell casting message to something which gets your attention.  Makes it easy to see amidst the spam.  Sorry, I don't have the specific number within eqclient.ini to change.<br>
<br>
3)  When you get really good, you can delay bashing until the mob is almost done casting the spell.  Remember, while a mob is casting, it isn't attacking.  So, bashing later can be helpful, but probably not enough to worry about.  What I do watch for is other interrupters.  Alot of times, a mob will begin casting another spell right after the first one is interrupted.  Usually, the bash skill has not reset by that time.  If there are other bashers or stunners present, I'll wait a second to see if the spell gets interrupted by someone else first.  If so, I save the bash for the next spell.<br>
<br>
You have been practicing your bash skill, right?<br>
<br>
Here are the screenshots.  I really should update them.  I think those weapons are the uber runed falcion and the ominous sharkjaw cutlass.<br>
<br>
