<br>
How many keys do you need?  Bash, taunt, disarm, incoming, sit (if you're lazy like me), beg maybe, kick...that's 7, and you won't be kicking and bashing together.  Incoming you can toss on another pad and jump back and forth, put a ranged weapon next to it.  So we're down to 5ish, which leaves room for the bash trick.  Set up an identical pad for non-bashing with any other keys you want.  Replace sit with /assist maybe?  For combat purposes you don't need Sense heading and so forth, move those onto a second pad along with Incoming and so forth.  Just a thought.<br>
<br>
If you're combining keys you should be even better off.  That kick/taunt/beg hotkey will work fine, just press it in between bashes since kick and bash don't work together.  You're looking at reassinging everything once maybe, to be the best warrior you can be?<br>
<br>
Just be glad you're not a bard, with their hotkey boxes.  Spells, plus swap spots, plus any special hotkeys they decide they need.<br>
<br>
Not trying to be legalistic here, I've been watching this thread for a bit now.  Just simple things that can be overcome.  Like, removing a certain loudmouthed mage to Tox!  (c'mere Kalyth...you can trust me...really...)<br>
